'''Aviad Meitar''' (born 1959) is the [[Chairman]] of Quadrant European Beverages Limited, the [[Pepsi]] [[bottling|bottler]] for [[Bulgaria]]. He served as Chairman of Quadrant Amorq Bottling Company Limited (QABCL), the exclusive [[PepsiCo]] licensee for [[Romania]] and [[Moldova]], until its successful sale to [[PepsiAmericas]], the second largest PepsiCo bottler in the world, in July 2006.<ref name="Capital">[http://www.capital.ro/index.php?section=articol&screen=index&id=132837 "'An Unimaginable Journey', de Aviad Meitar sau drumul spre succes a unei companii multinaţionale"], [[Capital (Romanian newspaper)|Capital]], March 10, 2010 ([https://translate.google.com/translate?js=n&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=2&eotf=1&sl=auto&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.capital.ro%2Findex.php%3Fsection%3Darticol%26screen%3Dindex%26id%3D132837 English])</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=3twmAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Aviad+Meitar%22&dq=%22Aviad+Meitar%22&hl=en&ei=I7yTTMaBL4T68Ab62sWrDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAg "Newsweek"], Volume 121, [[Newsweek]] Inc., 1993, Pg. 96</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=O5OZAAAAIAAJ&q=%22Aviad+Meitar%22&dq=%22Aviad+Meitar%22&hl=en&ei=I7yTTMaBL4T68Ab62sWrDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAw "Business international"], Volume 39, [[Business International Corporation|Business International Corp.]], 1981, Pg. 403</ref><ref>[http://www.amanet.org/training/podcasts/3595.aspx?pcode=XCRP "Aviad Meitar on Refreshing Romania with Pepsi"] Podcast, [[American Management Association]], May 28, 2010</ref>

Meitar set up QABCL's operation (Pepsi venture) in Romania in 1991 and has had oversight managerial responsibility for the company’s operations since.<ref name="Obiectiv">[http://www.obiectivdesuceava.ro/index.php?page=articol&ids=109675 "Istoria lansării Pepsi în România, în anii ´90, povestită de Aviad Meitar"], ''Obiectiv de Suceava'', March 12, 2010 ([https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=auto&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.obiectivdesuceava.ro%2Findex.php%3Fpage%3Darticol%26ids%3D109675 English])</ref><ref>Apetrei, Alina, [http://www.wall-street.ro/articol/English-Version/81851/Interview-The-story-of-Pepsi-Romania.html "Interview: The story of Pepsi Romania"], Wall-Street.ro, March 15, 2010</ref><ref>Fromm, Jeff, [http://businesslawstrategy.com/an-unimaginable-journey/favorite-quoted-quotes-from-an-unimaginable-journey "Favorite Quoted Quotes from ‘An Unimaginable Journey’"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100325090949/http://businesslawstrategy.com/an-unimaginable-journey/favorite-quoted-quotes-from-an-unimaginable-journey |date=2010-03-25 }}, Business Law Strategy, February 20, 2010</ref>

He has been a [[Senior management|senior executive]] with Quadrant Management, the [[New York City]]-based management arm of a private investment fund, for close to 18 years.  Prior to setting up QABCL he was responsible for other investments of the fund, and for the review of acquisition candidates.<ref name="Ziarul">[http://www.zf.ro/companii/sfatul-fondatorului-pepsi-pentru-antreprenorii-romani-vindeti-afacerea-inainte-de-a-ajunge-la-varf-5730436/ "Sfatul fondatorului Pepsi pentru antreprenorii romani: vindeti afacerea inainte de a ajunge la varf"], [[Ziarul Financiar]], March 10, 2010 ([https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=auto&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.zf.ro%2Fcompanii%2Fsfatul-fondatorului-pepsi-pentru-antreprenorii-romani-vindeti-afacerea-inainte-de-a-ajunge-la-varf-5730436%2F English])</ref>

==Biography==
Meitar grew up in a small town called [[Kiryat Ono]], in [[Israel]]. During his childhood years he studied in the local [[College or university school of music|conservatory]] and played the [[french horn]] in its [[concert band]]. This made music a special part of his life and, although he chose a different profession, he has been actively playing with concert bands and [[Orchestra|symphonic orchestras]] all these years.<ref name="Author" />

He has a [[Bachelor of Laws]] degree from [[Tel Aviv University]] School of Law and an [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] from [[Boston University]] Graduate School of Management.<ref name="Author">[http://aviadmeitar.com/theauthor/ "About the Author"]{{unreliable source?|date=July 2012}} {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100521025355/http://aviadmeitar.com/theauthor/ |date=May 21, 2010 }}, Aviad Meitar.com</ref><ref>[http://www.mmdnewswire.com/aviad-meitar-7375.html "New book describes how group of entrepreneurs navigated rough seas to bring one major American beverage company to emerging market economy of Romania"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714105852/http://www.mmdnewswire.com/aviad-meitar-7375.html |date=2011-07-14 }}, Newswire, March 9, 2010</ref>{{unreliable source?|date=July 2012}}

Meitar lives in Israel with his wife Ravit and has three children, Yigal, Ayal and Yiftach.<ref name="Author" />

