'''Boris Nemšić''' (born on August 17, 1957, in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]) is a Bosnian-Herzegovinian businessman and the former [[Chief Executive Officer|CEO]] of [[Telekom Austria]].<ref>{{cite book|url={{Google books|plainurl=y|id=aV80ZXSNUYEC|page=853}}|title= Club Carriere - Enzyklopädie des Erfolges 2001|publisher= [[Algoprint]]|isbn= 978-3-9521669-4-9|page= 853|language= German|date=December 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.forbes.com/feeds/afx/2009/03/02/afx6111927.html|title= Five facts about new Vimpelcom CEO Nemsic|date= 2009-03-02|accessdate= 2009-03-13|publisher= [[Forbes]]|agency= [[Reuters]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090309153249/http://www.forbes.com/feeds/afx/2009/03/02/afx6111927.html|archivedate=2009-03-09}}</ref> From April 2009 until June 2010 he was CEO of [[VimpelCom]].

He current holds various board member positions at the following companies: [[Delta Partners Group]] (Executive Board Member), I-New Unified Mobile Solutions (Chairman of the Board), Cellwize (Chairman of the Board) or [[Frequentis AG]] (Member of the Supervisory Board).<ref name="Boris">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/Research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=1458900&privcapId=35909078&previousCapId=1938237&previousTitle=Frequentis%20AG|title=Boris Nemsic Ph.D.|accessdate = 9 June 2016 |editor=Bloomberg}}</ref>

